	Abstract = {This paper studies the semantics of failure in distributed programming. We present a semantic model for distributed programs that use the standard sockets interface; it covers message loss, host failure and temporary disconnection, and supports reasoning about distributed infrastructure.We consider interaction via the UDP and ICMP protocols. To do this, it has been necessary to: 
